          <p class="lead">Is your <strong>heat pump not heating or cooling properly</strong>? Latour's HVAC provides fast, reliable <strong>heat pump repair</strong> for Lake Charles homeowners. Our NATE-certified technicians diagnose problems accurately and fix them right the first time—with most repairs completed the same day.</p>

          <p>Heat pumps are complex systems that require specialized knowledge to repair properly. Unlike standard air conditioners, heat pumps include a reversing valve and defrost controls that require expert diagnosis. Our technicians are trained specifically on heat pump systems and have the experience to get yours working again quickly.</p>

          <h2>Common Heat Pump Problems We Repair</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Heat Pump Not Heating:</strong> Could be a stuck reversing valve, low refrigerant, defrost issues, or thermostat problems</li>
            <li><strong>Heat Pump Not Cooling:</strong> Similar causes as cooling issues—refrigerant, airflow, or electrical problems</li>
            <li><strong>Heat Pump Running Constantly:</strong> May indicate low refrigerant, dirty coils, or incorrect sizing</li>
            <li><strong>Heat Pump Short Cycling:</strong> Turning on and off frequently often signals electrical issues or refrigerant problems</li>
            <li><strong>Ice Building Up:</strong> Defrost cycle problems, low refrigerant, or airflow restrictions</li>
            <li><strong>Heat Pump Making Noise:</strong> Grinding, squealing, or rattling indicate mechanical issues</li>
            <li><strong>Heat Pump Blowing Cold Air in Heat Mode:</strong> Reversing valve, refrigerant, or defrost issues</li>
            <li><strong>High Energy Bills:</strong> Efficiency problems often caused by refrigerant leaks or dirty components</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Heat Pump Brands We Service</h2>
